Create AWS Access Key
1. Access the AWS Console
1.	Log in to your account at aws.amazon.com/console.
2.	In the search bar at the top, type IAM and select the IAM Service.
2. Create a New IAM User
1.	On the left-hand sidebar, click Users.
2.	Click the Create user button.
3.	Enter a User name (e.g., devops-user).
4.	(Optional) Check "Provide user access to the AWS Management Console" if you want this user to be able to log in via a browser.
5.	Click Next.
3. Set Permissions
1.	Select Attach policies directly.
2.	Search for and check AdministratorAccess.
⚠️ Warning: For production environments, always follow the "Principle of Least Privilege." AdministratorAccess is used here for learning purposes only.
3.	Click Next, review your settings, and click Create user.
4. Generate Access Keys for CLI
1.	Click on your newly created user (devops-user) from the user list.
2.	Navigate to the Security credentials tab.
3.	Scroll down to the Access keys section and click Create access key.
4.	Select Command Line Interface (CLI) as your use case.
5.	Check the confirmation box and click Next.
6.	Click Create access key.
5. Secure Your Credentials
AWS will now display your Access Key ID and Secret Access Key.
•	Action: Click Download .csv file immediately.
•	Warning: This is the only time you can view or download the Secret Access Key. If you lose it, you will have to create a new one.

